that%20humans%20once%20performed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20that%20downturn%20isn't%20inevitable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225120%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ioana%20Marinescu%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F691b1220abd5e944effad717%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIoana%20Marinescu%20suggested%20that%20we%20may%20already%20be%20approaching%20the%20point%20where%20AI%20begins%20to%20suppress%20wages.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Ioana%20Marinescu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f34ade68-1759-400a-ba83-486db90fe82a%5C%22%3EWhere%20we%20are%20on%20the%20curve%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMarinescu%20estimates%20that%20more%20than%2014%25%20of%20%26quot%3Bintelligence%26quot%3B%20tasks%20are%20already%20automated%20%E2%80%94%20a%20figure%20based%20on%20research%20showing%20that%20routine%20cognitive%20jobs%20have%20declined%20from%2049%25%20in%20the%20late%201970s%20and%201980s%20to%2035%25%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20closer%20to%20a%20potential%20decline%20in%20wages%20than%20no%20automation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20baseline%20Brookings%20simulation%2C%20wages%20begin%20to%20fall%20when%20about%2037%25%20of%20intelligence%20tasks%20are%20automated%20%E2%80%94%20a%20threshold%20that%20could%20arrive%20sooner%20than%20many%20expect%20if%20AI%20adoption%20continues%20to%20accelerate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20there's%20no%20broad%20sign%20of%20that%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20too%20early%20to%20tell%2C%26quot%3B%20Marinescu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20she%20pointed%20to%20%26quot%3Bsuggestive%20evidence%26quot%3B%20that%20less-experienced%20workers%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-politics-professor-shares-jobs-least-likely-be-automated-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI-exposed%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20already%20being%20displaced%2C%20citing%20a%20recent%20study%20by%20Stanford.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftheres-more-bad-news-for-entry-level-coders-ai-study-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eearly-career%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ages%2022%20to%2025%2C%20in%20AI-exposed%20occupations%20such%20as%20software%20development%20and%20customer%20service%20have%20experienced%20a%2013%25%20decline%20in%20employment%20since%20the%20rise%20of%20generative%20AI%2C%20whereas%20employment%20for%20older%20and%20less-exposed%20workers%20has%20remained%20stable%20or%20increased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20Marinescu%20added%2C%20the%20real%20warning%20sign%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20noticeable%20reduction%20in%20the%20overall%20share%20of%20intelligence%20jobs%26quot%3B%20across%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20the%20moment%20the%20labor%20market%20begins%20to%20reallocate%20toward%20more%20physical%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b618dc88-6ed4-4b4b-b302-f0084804f3a0%5C%22%3EWhy%20a%20wage%20downturn%20isn't%20inevitable%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMarinescu%20said%20that%20the%20outcome%20depends%20on%20how%20society%20manages%20the%20transition%20between%20the%20%26quot%3Bphysical%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bintelligence%26quot%3B%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20the%20two%20%5Bsectors%5D%20are%20complements%2C%20like%20labor%20and%20capital%20%E2%80%94%20i.e.%2C%20you%20need%20some%20of%20both%20to%20produce%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAutomation%20is%20more%20likely%20to%20yield%20steady%20wage%20increases%20with%20complementarity%3B%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20long-run%20gains%20from%20adding%20more%20AI%20in%20the%20economy%20saturate%20under%20complementarity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20AI%20and%20human%20labor%20can%20raise%20productivity%20together%20%E2%80%94%20but%20only%20if%20automation%20is%20paired%20with%20real-world%20investment%20that%20keeps%20workers%20essential%20to%20the%20production%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Brookings%20paper%20said%20that%20the%20economy's%20physical%20side%20%E2%80%94%20the%20factories%2C%20hospitals%2C%20construction%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20that%20AI%20still%20can't%20automate%20%E2%80%94%20must%20keep%20pace%20with%20intelligence-sector%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20prevent%20a%20wage%20collapse%2C%20the%20authors%20propose%20slowing%20the%20pace%20of%20automation%20and%20boosting%20investment%20in%20physical%20capital%2C%20ensuring%20that%20embodied%20work%20remains%20productive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20suggest%20taxing%20virtual%20labor%20to%20encourage%20companies%20to%20maintain%20a%20healthy%20balance%20between%20machine%20and%20human%20production%20%E2%80%94%20a%20proposal%20similar%20to%20Sen.%20Bernie%20Sanders'%20call%20for%20imposing%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbernie-sanders-robot-tax-ai-worker-report-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erobot%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20on%20companies%20that%20adopt%20AI%20to%20replace%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20uncertainty%2C%20Marinescu%20added%2C%20lies%20in%20how%20substitutable%20AI%20and%20human%20output%20become.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20AI%20ultimately%20replaces%20most%20intelligence%20work%2C%20wage%20growth%20is%20likely%20to%20flatten.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20humans%20and%20machines%20remain%20complementary%20%E2%80%94%20each%20amplifying%20the%20other's%20output%20%E2%80%94%20the%20economy%20could%20continue%20to%20expand%20without%20leaving%20workers%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-wage-gains-could-peak-soon-professor-on-solutions-investment-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1764160791000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6926d401e1a9cbb014df036f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C