or-manufacturing-rare-earth-permanent-magnets-why-its-important%2Farticleshow%2F125587134.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20is%20set%20to%20significantly%20bolster%20its%20rare%20earth%20magnet%20production%20with%20the%20Union%20Cabinet%20approving%20a%20Rs%207%2C280%20crore%20scheme.%20This%20pioneering%20initiative%20aims%20to%20establish%20integrated%20manufacturing%20facilities%2C%20boosting%20domestic%20capacity%20to%206%2C000%20metric%20tons%20annually.%20The%20seven-year%20plan%20focuses%20on%20the%20entire%20value%20chain%2C%20from%20oxides%20to%20finished%20magnets%2C%20enhancing%20India's%20strategic%20self-reliance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20BUSINESS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fatmanirbhar-bharat-boost-for-rare-earths-cabinet-clears-rs-7200-crore-scheme-for-manufacturing-rare-earth-permanent-magnets-why-its-important%2Farticleshow%2F125587134.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22We're%20Americans%20who've%20traveled%20to%2012%20countries%20this%20year%20doing%20the%20'Schengen%20shuffle.'%20Here's%20how%20it%20works.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Eric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F692381e789026fbb4d0e3d6a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman%20practice%20the%20%26quot%3BSchengen%20shuffle.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EEric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20'Schengen%20shuffle'%20allows%20non-EU%20citizens%20to%20stay%20in%20Europe%20for%20extended%20periods%20of%20time.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman%2C%20both%20Americans%2C%20have%20made%20Italy%20their%20base%20since%202022.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20best%20of%20both%20worlds%20for%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Christina%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-americans-move-to-italy-affordable-healthcare-work-life-balance-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20who%20left%20the%20US%20in%202022%20to%20retire%20in%20Italy.%20The%20couple%20now%20does%20the%20%26quot%3BSchengen%20shuffle.%26quot%3B%20Schengen%20countries%20allow%20non-EU%20visitors%20to%20stay%20for%20up%20to%2090%20days%20within%20a%20180-day%20period.%20The%20%26quot%3BSchengen%20shuffle%26quot%3B%20refers%20to%20the%20practice%20of%20non-EU%20travelers%20hopping%20between%20both%20Schengen%20and%20non-Schengen%20countries%20indefinitely.%20This%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChristina%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20had%20gotten%20our%20elective%20residency%20visas%2C%20which%20allowed%20us%20to%20live%20in%20Italy%20full%20time.%20Those%20were%20valid%20for%20two%20years%2C%20so%20after%20that%20period%20was%20up%2C%20we%20decided%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%20that%20we%20wouldn't%20renew%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEric%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20lot%20of%20the%20motivation%20was%20that%20we're%20traveling%20so%20much%20and%20we%20want%20to%20see%20so%20much%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChristina%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20started%20the%20Schengen%20shuffle%20in%20December%202024.%20There%20are%2029%20countries%20in%20the%20Schengen%20Agreement%2C%20which%20essentially%20are%20countries%20in%20Europe%20that%20allow%20free%20and%20open%20borders%20between%20them.%20So%2C%20if%20we%20want%20to%20drive%20from%20Italy%20to%20France%2C%20we%20don't%20go%20through%20passport%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20decided%20we%20wanted%20to%20do%20that%20instead%20of%20being%20full-time%20residents%20of%20Italy.%20Italy%20is%20one%20of%20the%2029%20countries%20in%20the%20Schengen%20area%2C%20so%20we%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20we%20can%20keep%20our%20house%20in%20Italy%2C%20stay%20there%20for%2090%20days%2C%20then%20go%20travel%20for%2090%20days%2C%20and%20come%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20best%20of%20both%20worlds%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a22ccb8c-1b07-4258-980e-e4d7939b31f7%5C%22%3EThe%20Schwendemans%20have%20visited%20around%2012%20new%20countries%20this%20year%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Eric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69238272e1a9cbb014deccbf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman%20traveled%20to%20India.%3Cp%3EEric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEric%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We've%20seen%20around%2012%20new%20countries%20this%20year%2C%20far%20and%20wide%2C%20from%20Southeast%20Asia%20to%20the%20Balkans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20Thailand%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20Cambodia.%20We%20went%20to%20Hong%20Kong%20and%20Macau.%20Then%2C%20we%20flew%20down%20to%20the%20Philippines%20for%20two%20weeks.%20We%20spent%20almost%20two%20weeks%20in%20India%20and%20then%20came%20home%20to%20Italy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20things%20that%20we%20committed%20to%20was%20spending%20ample%20time%20in%20areas%20that%20allow%20us%20to%20see%20it%2C%20to%20experience%20it%2C%20and%20give%20ourselves%20days%20of%20rest%20in%20between%2C%20instead%20of%20just%20racing%20nonstop%2024%2F7.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChristina%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt%20allows%20you%20to%20become%20more%20a%20part%20of%20communities%20and%20%E2%80%94%20I%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20use%20this%20phrase%20%E2%80%94%20more%20of%20a%20traveler%20than%20a%20tourist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20great%20example%20for%20us%20is%20that%20we%20spent%20a%20month%20in%20Perast%2C%20Montenegro.%20It's%20a%20very%20small%20town.%20By%20the%20time%20we%20left%2C%20we%20knew%20everyone.%20Like%20Eric%20said%2C%20we%20made%20friends%20that%20we've%20seen%20again%20since%20we%20left.%20We%20could%20go%20into%20any%20restaurant%20and%20know%20everybody%20by%20name.%20To%20be%20able%20to%20do%20that%20in%20a%20different%20community%20is%20just%20something%20really%20special.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222675%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Eric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F692382c5e1a9cbb014deccc9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222006%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChristina%20and%20Eric%20Schwendeman%20left%20the%20United%20States%20in%202022.%3Cp%3EEric%20and%20Christina%20Schwendeman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEric%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20would%20say%20that%2085%25%20of%20the%20time%20we're%20staying%20in%20Airbnbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChristina%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIf%20you%20get%20an%20Airbnb%20with%20your%20own%20kitchen%2C%20you%20can%20go%20grocery%20shopping%20and%20cook%20at%20home.%20That%20makes%20a%20big%20difference%20for%20us.%20If%20we're%20staying%20anywhere%20longer%20than%20a%20week%2C%20it's%20Airbnb%20because%20we%20want%20to%20feel%20like%20we%20have%20a%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETransportation%20can%20get%20tricky%2C%20but%20we%20try%20not%20to%20fly%20a%20lot%20because%20it's%20obviously%20the%20most%20expensive%20option.%20A%20lot%20of%20countries%20have%20phenomenal%20train%20systems%2C%20so%20we%20try%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20those.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20packing%20is%20interesting.%20For%2090%20days%20at%20a%20time%2C%20we%20committed%20to%20each%20other%20that%20we%20would%20only%20each%20take%20one%20medium-sized%20suitcase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222983d9a8-293e-42